==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sabotage
<hw>Sa`bo`tage"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Scamped work.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Malicious waste or destruction of an employer's property or injury
to his interests by workmen during labor troubles.</def></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>any surreptitious destruction of property or
obstruction of activity by persons not known to be hostile; -- in war,
such actions carried out behind enemy lines by agents or local
sympathisers of the hostile power.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sabotiere</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
